  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\nFutures pointing modestly higher across the board with S&P 500 at $701.66 (+0.25%) as Iran peace deal hopes keep risk-on sentiment alive. VIX sitting elevated at 29.3 suggests markets still pricing geopolitical risk despite the optimism. Tech and Energy leading the charge while Healthcare drags - classic risk-on rotation in play.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Building Permits</strong> (12:30 ET) - Housing data critical with rates still elevated and affordability concerns mounting</li>\n<li><strong>Fed Speeches</strong> - Barkin (4:15 PM) and Waller (6:00 PM) could signal policy direction ahead of next meeting</li>\n<li><strong>Bank Earnings</strong> - ALLY, STT, FITB all reporting BMO; watch net interest margin guidance closely</li>\n<li><strong>Baker Hughes Rig Count</strong> (5:00 PM) - Energy names ripping, production data matters for momentum</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\nClear risk-on move with Tech (+1.14%) and Energy (+1.47%) leading while defensive Healthcare (-0.79%) and Staples lagging. Real Estate (+0.92%) getting bid on rate cut hopes tied to potential Iran resolution. This rotation only works if geopolitical tensions actually ease - watch oil and dollar for confirmation.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Iran peace deal momentum accelerates risk-on rotation, VIX collapses below 25, and tech multiples expand on lower rate expectations</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>Peace talks stall over weekend, oil spikes Monday, and this relief rally gets sold into resistance at SPY $705</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Dollar weakness (second weekly drop) fueling commodity and international exposure trades - watch DXY 103 support</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY $705</strong> - Key resistance from March highs, break above opens $715</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ $645</strong> - Clean breakout level, tech leadership needs to hold here</li>\n<li><strong>VIX 27</strong> - Break below signals real de-risking, watch for vol crush</li>\n<li><strong>XLE $95</strong> - Energy at critical breakout, failure here kills the momentum trade</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
